        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tls): add subjectAltName to auto-generated gateway self-signed certificate (fixes #96910)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #96910.\n\nWhen gateway TLS is enabled with `autoGenerate=true`, the self-signed certificate had no `subjectAltName` extension. Node.js ≥17 ignores the CN for hostname/IP verification per RFC 6125, causing CLI probe to `wss://127.0.0.1:18789` to fail.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n- New certs: Added `-addext subjectAltName=DNS:localhost,DNS:<hostname>,IP:127.0.0.1,IP:::1` to the openssl command\n- Existing certs: Auto-detect CN-only certs (`CN=openclaw-gateway`, no SAN) and regenerate with SANs\n- Transactional upgrade: old files renamed to `.bak`, restored on failure\n- Custom certs (non-OpenClaw CN) are never touched\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **Unit tests:** `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/infra/tls/gateway.test.ts` — 10/10 passed\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n```\n# New cert: SAN verified via openssl\n$ openssl x509 -in gateway-cert.pem -noout -ext subjectAltName\nX509v3 Subject Alternative Name:\n    DNS:localhost, DNS:LIN-66D8BD4EA2C, IP Address:127.0.0.1, IP Address:0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1\n\n# Strict TLS check passes\n$ node -e \"tls.checkServerIdentity('127.0.0.1', cert)\"\n✅ STRICT TLS CHECK PASSED for 127.0.0.1\n\n# Upgrade path: CN-only cert auto-detected and regenerated\n[warn] gateway tls: upgrading CN-only certificate to include subjectAltName\n[info] gateway tls: generated self-signed cert at ...\n\n# Custom cert not touched\nBEFORE: CN=custom-server, no SAN\nAFTER:  CN=custom-server, no SAN (unchanged)\n```\n\n- ✅ New certs include subjectAltName\n- ✅ Strict TLS identity check passes for IP and hostname\n- ✅ Existing CN-only certs auto-upgraded with transactional backup/rollback\n- ✅ Custom certificates (non-OpenClaw) are never rewritten\n\n- [x] AI-assisted",
